<font face=helvetica size=3><b>Monday July 10, 2000</b></font>
			<hr align=LEFT size=1 width=500 color=#000080>
<!---------------news---------------->
<Br>
<font face=helvetica size=2 color=#000080><b>Hosted Site Updates</b> - 10:33:16</font>
<br><br><blockquote>
Ok, I'm a day late, take it up with the boss.<br><br>

<li><a href=http://3dmr.gamedesign.net/>The 3D Map Realm</a> has updated with some reasons why there have been few updates lately, and a promise to have some new content this week.</li> 
<li><a href=http://buzzsaw.gamedesign.net/>Buzzsaw</a>, your source for real-world game design, has some new Quake 1 textures, an ask for help, and a contest cancellation.</li> 
<li>There is a ton of news at the <a href=http://halflife.gamedesign.net/>HalfLife Editing Resource Center</a>, so much that I don't even want to try to list it all. If you're making maps for Half-Life (or TFC or Counterstrike), go there now.</li> 
<li><a href=http://info.gamedesign.net/>Info_Design</a> has a new prefab, news of a new TFC editing mailing list, and a new map.</li> 
<li><a href=http://oshlm.gamedesign.net/>Open Source Half-Life Maps</a> has word of feedback received, site changes, and instructions for would-be contributors. </li>
<li><a href=http://qoole.gamedesign.net/>Qoole:Pursuit of Perfection</a> has some good news and some bad news about v0.99 of Qoole.</li> 
<li><a href=http://qw3.gamedesign.net/>Q-Workshop 3</a> has news of the site baton being passed again, from DrQube to Crashmeplease. There's also quite a bit of news, and check out the Maya Project while you're there.</li> 
<li>Like the Half-Life ERC, <a href=http://unreal.gamedesign.net/>Wolf's Unreal</a> has quite a bit of news, so you should probably just go there and check it out.</li>

Ok, there you go. Check out the hosted sites, and by the way, send more pics for the POTD. 


<b><p align=right>Update by <a href="mailto:iamfury@gamedesign.net">Fury</a></p></b>
</blockquote>
<h3>Go <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net">back</a> to the main news page...</h3>
